race.comment: HIMENO (10) debuts for the Payne yard and has been well educated. Placed at Sandown Hillside in his most recent trial and maps okay. Looks ready to go and this is winnable. IGOTMYMINDONYOU (1) progressed nicely last time to finish just 0.8 lengths from the winner over 1000m at Yarra Valley. Draws to sit close up again and has the talent to take this out.  SNAPPY BEAU (2) resumes and has raced well in stronger Maidens. He's jumped out well at Seymour and on song he will be right in the finish. BOLD AMORE (12) resumes and won a recent Werribee jumpout. Has a handy claim and no surprise to see him much improved. POINTS FOR EFFORT (4)  resumes and he was narrowly beaten at Seymour two back. He's jumped out and is likely to race well.
